    • Method Detail

      • start

        public void start()
           throws ImplifyException
        Starts the current Implify instance. It will start a new thread, which will start other threads if needed. Exceptions will be handled by an ExceptionHandler, which can be changed with setExceptionHandler(ExceptionHandler)
        Throws:
        ImplifyException - if instance already running or an I/O error occurs.

      • stop

        public void stop()
          throws ImplifyException
        Stops current implify instance.
        Throws:
        ImplifyException - if instance not running or an I/O error occurs.
